The paper deals with the problem of providing secrecy in communication systems, which is a central topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of lattice codes is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to coding theory (cs.CR) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of cooperative jamming, which is a technique commonly used in wireless communication systems (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of securing communication in multi-hop networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of network security (cs.NI).
